## Example 4: Student Grades with Error Handling

**Scenario:** Process student grades with error handling

```javascript
const gradesCSV = `student_id,name,math,english,science,average
1,"Alice Smith",95,92,98,95.0
2,"Bob Johnson",87,91,85,87.67
3,"Charlie Brown",92,88,"unclosed quote
4,"Diana Prince",98,95,96,96.33`;

const result = parseCSV(gradesCSV);

// Check for parsing errors
if (result.errors.length > 0) {
  console.log('Warning: Some rows had parsing errors:');
  result.errors.forEach(err => {
    console.log(`  Row ${err.row}: ${err.message}`);
  });
  // Warning: Some rows had parsing errors:
  //   Row 4: Unclosed quoted field
}

// Process valid rows
console.log(`Successfully loaded ${result.count()} student records\n`);
// Successfully loaded 3 student records

// Get top performers
const topStudents = result
  .filter(row => row.average >= 95)
  .rows
  .sort((a, b) => b.average - a.average);

console.log('Top Students:');
topStudents.forEach(student => {
  console.log(`  ${student.name}: ${student.average.toFixed(2)}`);
});
// Top Students:
//   Alice Smith: 95.00
//   Diana Prince: 96.33

// Calculate class statistics
console.log('\nClass Statistics:');
console.log(`Math average: ${result.average('math').toFixed(2)}`);
console.log(`English average: ${result.average('english').toFixed(2)}`);
console.log(`Science average: ${result.average('science').toFixed(2)}`);
// Class Statistics:
// Math average: 93.00
// English average: 91.50
// Science average: 93.00
```

---

## Example 5: Product Inventory with Custom Delimiters

**Scenario:** Import inventory from semicolon-delimited file

```javascript
// European format with semicolons
const inventoryCSV = `sku;name;quantity;price;supplier
SKU001;Laptop Computer;150;899.99;"Acme Corp, USA"
SKU002;USB Mouse;500;29.99;"Tech Supplies, Inc"
SKU003;Keyboard;300;79.99;"Global Tech, Ltd"
SKU004;Monitor;75;299.99;"Display Masters, USA"
SKU005;Desk Chair;100;249.99;"Furniture Group, Inc"`;

const result = parseCSV(inventoryCSV, { delimiter: ';' });

// Calculate inventory value
const inventoryValue = result.rows.reduce((sum, item) => {
  return sum + (item.quantity * item.price);
}, 0);

console.log(`Total inventory value: $${inventoryValue.toFixed(2)}`);
// Total inventory value: $244574.50

// Find low stock items (less than 100)
const lowStock = result.filter(row => row.quantity < 100);
console.log(`\nLow stock items:`);
lowStock.rows.forEach(item => {
  console.log(`  ${item.sku}: ${item.name} (${item.quantity} units)`);
});
// Low stock items:
//   SKU004: Monitor (75 units)

// Calculate average inventory per category (all items in this case)
const avgQty = result.average('quantity');
console.log(`\nAverage stock level: ${avgQty.toFixed(0)} units`);
// Average stock level: 225 units

// Total value by price range
const expensive = result.filter(row => row.price > 200);
const expensiveValue = expensive.rows.reduce((sum, item) => 
  sum + (item.quantity * item.price), 0);

console.log(`\nHigh-value items (>$200): $${expensiveValue.toFixed(2)}`);
// High-value items (>$200): $224549.50
```

---

## Example 6: Weather Data Analysis

**Scenario:** Analyze temperature and precipitation data

```javascript
const weatherCSV = `date,city,temperature,humidity,precipitation
2024-01-01,New York,28,65,0.5
2024-01-01,Los Angeles,58,45,0.0
2024-01-01,Chicago,22,70,1.2
2024-01-02,New York,30,68,0.0
2024-01-02,Los Angeles,62,40,0.0
2024-01-02,Chicago,25,72,0.8
2024-01-03,New York,32,60,0.0
2024-01-03,Los Angeles,65,35,0.0
2024-01-03,Chicago,28,65,0.0`;

const result = parseCSV(weatherCSV);

// Temperature statistics
const avgTemp = result.average('temperature');
console.log(`Average temperature: ${avgTemp.toFixed(1)}В°F`);
// Average temperature: 38.9В°F

// Precipitation analysis
const rainyDays = result.filter(row => row.precipitation > 0);
console.log(`Rainy days: ${rainyDays.count()} out of ${result.count()}`);
// Rainy days: 2 out of 9

// Group by city
const byCity = result.groupBy('city');
for (const [city, readings] of byCity) {
  const temps = readings.map(r => r.temperature);
  const avgTemp = temps.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / temps.length;
  const totalPrecip = readings.reduce((sum, r) => sum + r.precipitation, 0);
  console.log(`${city}: avg temp ${avgTemp.toFixed(1)}В°F, total precipitation ${totalPrecip.toFixed(1)}"`);
}
// New York: avg temp 30.0В°F, total precipitation 0.5"
// Los Angeles: avg temp 61.7В°F, total precipitation 0.0"
// Chicago: avg temp 25.0В°F, total precipitation 2.0"

// Find warmest readings
const warmest = result
  .rows
  .sort((a, b) => b.temperature - a.temperature)
  .slice(0, 3);

console.log(`\nWarmest readings:`);
warmest.forEach(reading => {
  console.log(`  ${reading.city}: ${reading.temperature}В°F`);
});
// Warmest readings:
//   Los Angeles: 65В°F
//   Los Angeles: 62В°F
//   Los Angeles: 58В°F
```

