## Example 7: Survey Results with Boolean and Null Handling

**Scenario:** Process survey responses with mixed data types

```javascript
const surveyCSV = `respondent_id,age,satisfaction,would_recommend,feedback
1,25,true,true,"Great product!"
2,34,true,true,
3,28,false,false,"Not what I expected"
4,45,true,null,"Good but expensive"
5,31,false,false,
6,29,true,true,"Excellent service"""`;

const result = parseCSV(surveyCSV);

// Satisfaction rate
const satisfied = result.filter(row => row.satisfaction === true);
const satisfactionRate = (satisfied.count() / result.count()) * 100;
console.log(`Satisfaction rate: ${satisfactionRate.toFixed(1)}%`);
// Satisfaction rate: 50.0%

// Recommendation rate (excluding nulls)
const wouldRecommend = result.filter(row => row.would_recommend === true);
console.log(`Would recommend: ${wouldRecommend.count()} out of ${result.count()}`);
// Would recommend: 2 out of 6

// Average age
const avgAge = result.average('age');
console.log(`Average respondent age: ${avgAge.toFixed(1)} years`);
// Average respondent age: 32.0 years

// Feedback analysis
const withFeedback = result.filter(row => row.feedback !== null && row.feedback !== '');
console.log(`\nFeedback provided by ${withFeedback.count()} respondents:`);
withFeedback.rows.forEach(response => {
  console.log(`  ${response.feedback}`);
});
// Feedback provided by 4 respondents:
//   Great product!
//   Not what I expected
//   Good but expensive
//   Excellent service

// Segment by satisfaction
const segments = result.groupBy('satisfaction');
console.log(`\nSatisfied customers: ${segments.get('true')?.length || 0}`);
console.log(`Unsatisfied customers: ${segments.get('false')?.length || 0}`);
// Satisfied customers: 3
// Unsatisfied customers: 3
```

---

## Example 8: Tab-Separated Values (TSV)

**Scenario:** Parse tab-separated file (common in bioinformatics)

```javascript
const tsvData = `gene_id	gene_name	chromosome	start	end	strand
ENSG00001	BRCA1	chr17	43044295	43170245	-
ENSG00002	TP53	chr17	7565097	7590856	+
ENSG00003	EGFR	chr7	55086714	55324313	+
ENSG00004	MYC	chr8	127735434	127742951	+`;

const result = parseCSV(tsvData, { delimiter: '\t' });

console.log(`Loaded ${result.count()} genes\n`);
// Loaded 4 genes

// Genes on chromosome 17
const chr17 = result.filter(row => row.chromosome === 'chr17');
console.log(`Genes on chromosome 17: ${chr17.count()}`);
// Genes on chromosome 17: 2

// Gene location information
result.rows.forEach(gene => {
  const length = gene.end - gene.start;
  console.log(`${gene.gene_name}: ${length.toLocaleString()} bp on ${gene.chromosome}`);
});
// BRCA1: 125,950 bp on chr17
// TP53: 25,759 bp on chr17
// EGFR: 237,599 bp on chr7
// MYC: 7,517 bp on chr8

// Forward strand genes
