### Example 6: Filtering

```javascript
const csv = `product,category,price,rating
Apple,Fruit,1.50,4.8
Banana,Fruit,0.75,4.5
Carrot,Vegetable,0.50,4.2
Steak,Meat,15.99,4.9`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// Single filter
const highRated = result.filter(row => row.rating >= 4.8);
console.log(highRated.count());  // 2

// Chained filters
